            <div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2023_01">
                
                <p>This is the 7th year of Kōrājarākesarivarman. Rājarājapallavaraiyaṉ alias Ampalavaṉ Paḻuvūr Nakkaṉ, lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyaṉ</foreign></supplied> of Ku<supplied reason="lost">vaḷḷālam</supplied>, of the superior grade <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>peruntiṟattu</foreign></supplied> of the Lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyār</foreign></supplied>, who graciously caused to raise <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eḻuntaruḷḷuvitta</foreign></supplied> in stone the sanctuary <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>śrī- vimāṉam</foreign></supplied> for Śrī Vijayamaṅgalatēvar of big Śrī-Vā<supplied reason="lost">ṉa</supplied>vaṉ-mahādevi-<supplied reason="lost">catur</supplied>vedimaṅgalam, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of the northern bank; having graciously caused to raise <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eḻuntaruḷḷuvittu</foreign></supplied> the sanctuary <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vimāṉam</foreign></supplied> of this temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ikkōyil</foreign></supplied>, the weight of two hundred <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s of gold <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> sent for the jewels <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruvāparaṇattuku</foreign></supplied> for Kūttaperumāḷ and Umābhaṭṭāl, were given <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p></div>
            
